
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ipod-read-sysinfo-extended` baraye khandan etela'at bishtar va joz'iyat systemi az yek iPod estefade mishavad. In dastoor etela'ati mesl version firmware, serial number va digar moshakhasat sakht afzari ra namayesh midahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor va gozine-haye an.
    🔹 `--output <file>`  --> 💾 Zakhire kardan etela'at be yek file khass.
    🔹 `--verbose`  --> 🗣️ Namayesh etela'at bishtar dar morede process.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ipod-read-sysinfo-extended

    🔹 Khandan va namayesh etela'at systemi iPod be soorat standart.

    $ ipod-read-sysinfo-extended --output sysinfo.txt

    🔹 Khandan etela'at systemi iPod va zakhire kardan an dar file `sysinfo.txt`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ipod-read-sysinfo-extended --verbose

    🔹 Etela'at systemi iPod ra ba tafsilat bishtar namayesh midahad, shamel message-haye debug va etela'at dar morede har marhale az process.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ipod-read-sysinfo-extended` command is used to read extended system information from an iPod. This command displays information such as the firmware version, serial number, and other hardware specifications.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Display the command's help information and options.
    🔹 `--output <file>`  --> 💾 Save the information to a specific file.
    🔹 `--verbose`  --> 🗣️ Display more detailed information about the process.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ipod-read-sysinfo-extended

    🔹 Read and display the iPod's system information in standard output.

    $ ipod-read-sysinfo-extended --output sysinfo.txt

    🔹 Read the iPod's system information and save it to the `sysinfo.txt` file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ ipod-read-sysinfo-extended --verbose

    🔹 Displays the iPod's system information with more details, including debug messages and information about each step of the process.

